                                <condition>
                                    <p>The lower margin is for the most part torn or crumbled away
                                        and two of the majuscules has had a copper connection that
                                        has corroded the vellum in an Þ and S shape. In some places
                                        of f. 1v, most probably because of a former use as binding,
                                        the parchment has become so dark or the writing so
                                        indistinct that reading is difficult.</p>
