                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1301" notAfter="1325" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>The manuscript is written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>. <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name> (<bibl>
                                    <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">KKKat</ref>
                                </bibl>)has dated it to <origDate>the fourteenth century</origDate>,
                                whereas <name type="person" key="OleWid001">Ole Widding</name>
                                        (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary" target="HandskrWidding1960">Widding 1960</ref>, p. 91</bibl>) and <name type="person" key="SteKar001">Stefán Karlsson</name> (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary" target="EIMF7">Stéfan Karlsson 1967</ref>,
                                    p. 59</bibl>) respectively, have dated it more precisely to
                                    <origDate notBefore="1300" notAfter="1325" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">first quarter of the fourteenth
                                    century</origDate>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The only known owner of the leaf is the Priest <name type="person" key="MagMar001">Magnús Markússon</name>
                     </p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>On the top margin of f. 1r Árni Magnússon has written: <q>frä Sr
                                    Magnuse Markussyne 1725</q>.</p>
